{"question":"\r\n<div class='question' style='padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;'>\r\n<p align=\"LEFT\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">A factory makes lamps. The probability that a lamp is defective is 0.05. A random </span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">sample of 30 lamps is tested.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">Find the probability that there is at least one defective lamp in the sample.</span></p>\r\n<div class='marks'>[4]</div>\r\n<div class='question_part_label'>a.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class='question' style='padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;'>\r\n<p align=\"LEFT\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">A factory makes lamps. The probability that a lamp is defective is 0.05. A random </span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">sample of 30 lamps is tested.</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"LEFT\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">Given that there is at least one defective lamp in the sample, find the probability </span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">that there are at most two defective lamps.</span></p>\r\n<div class='marks'>[4]</div>\r\n<div class='question_part_label'>b.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n","markschems":"\r\n<div class='question' style='padding-left: 20px;'>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">evidence of recognizing binomial (seen anywhere)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1) </strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">e.g. \\({\\rm{B}}(n{\\text{, }}p)\\), \\({0.95^{30}}\\)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">finding \\({\\rm{P}}(X = 0) = 0.21463876\\)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong> </em></span></p>\r\